article.headline: Osetkowski leads Texas over S. Dakota St. 79-73 in NIT

images.name: Flatten drops the one-handed hammer
images.caption: Skylar Flatten takes off for a one-handed jam in the lane for South Dakota State.

article.linkText: Osetkowski leads Texas over S. Dakota St. 79-73 in NIT
article.story: AUSTIN, Texas -- Dylan Osetkowski had a career-high 26 points as Texas defeated South Dakota State 79-73 in the NIT first round on Tuesday night. Osetkowski shot 4 for 6 from beyond the arc. Courtney Ramey had 13 points for Texas (17-16). Kerwin Roach II added 12 points. Mike Daum had 25 points and 11 rebounds for the Jackrabbits (24-9). David Jenkins Jr. added 19 points. Skyler Flatten had 14 points and six rebounds. --- For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/Collegebasketball and http://twitter.com/AP-Top25 --- This was generated by Automated Insights, http://www.automatedinsights.com/ap, using data from STATS LLC, https://www.stats.com

videos.headline: Daum achieves a milestone and gets it done on both ends
videos.description: Mike Daum hit a tough shot to move up to eight on the NCAA all-time scoring list then gets a huge block on the other end of the court for South Dakota State.
